    "longBusinessSummary": "Duc Giang Chemicals Group Joint Stock Company, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures industrial products in Vietnam. It offers detergent, laundry detergent liquid, floor cleaner, javel, hand wash, fabric softener, toilet cleaner, and hand washing gel; DAP, NPK, and DSP fertilizer, as well as mono ammonium phosphate and single superphosphate; TIA sang battery, such as sealed industrial batteries, civil batteries, and MF maintenance-free starting battery cars; sealed battery; dry charged starting battery for cars and boats; and ferro and yellow phosphorus. The company also provides chemical industry products, such as natri hexametha phosphate; food and industrial alcohol; clohydric and sulfuric acid; amoni and ammonium hydroxide; natri phosphate; zinc granular; electronic phosphoric acid; kali dihydro photphat KH2PO4; acetic acid; natri hydroxit; and natri hexamethaphosphat liquid. In addition, it engages in the production and trading of raw materials and chemical goods; rubber, paint, plastic, fertilizer, iron, steel, and non-ferrous metal products; manufacture and trade of machinery, electrical equipment and components, electrical materials, and mechanical tools; producing and trading of mineral fuels, mineral oil, and distillation products; substances; and mineral waxes. Further, the company is involved in factory leases; freight transport by road; wholesale of food additives; exploiting, exploring, and processing minerals; and real estate activities. The company was formerly known as Duc Giang Chemicals And Detergent Powder Joint Stock Company and changed its name to Duc Giang Chemicals Group Joint Stock Company in April 2019. The company was founded in 1963 and is based in Hanoi, Vietnam.",
